news.title: Maharashtra: Citizens propose regulatory authority for redevelopment projects
news.para: The MSWA has written to the minister with a proposal for regulatory authority to focus on the redevelopment of housing societies.

news.title: Layout revised, government panel wants work to resume on Noida Sports City after two years
news.para: The Noida Authority had in 2021 ordered a stay on all construction work related to the project after the Comptroller and Auditor General (CAG) raised objections on the earlier layout.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso buyers demand revision of buyback rates for flats
news.para: Also, before starting demolition of towers D,E, F and G as ordered by the district administration, residents have sought a guaranteed bond for safety of towers A, B, C and J from Chintels.

news.title: Mumbai: Srinath Builders' directors arrested for failing to hand over flat
news.para: Police said the complainant had paid Niraj nearly Rs 3.3 crore for a 1,620 sq ft flat in a housing project in Ghatkopar over the last three years, but the builder failed to complete the project in time and hand over possession of the flat.

news.title: Greater Noida homebuyers take registry protest to Jantar Mantar
news.para: After a year-long protest at Ek Murti Chowk, homebuyers alleged that no action had been taken on the pending registries and completion of stalled projects.

news.title: AQI lens zooms in on large real estate projects in Delhi
news.para: A senior government official said the companies would have to send Google coordinates which will be examined by the ground staff of environment and other agencies from time to time.

news.title: Air India leases 620,000 sq ft in Gurugram for training centre
news.para: The airline will pay an annual rental of about Rs 60 crore, and it has leased the property for a period of 21 years, said people close to the development.

news.title: Funds released to develop New Kanpur City, Bingawan scheme
news.para: On Friday, the Kanpur Development Authority (KDA) officials held a meeting and made a decision to formalise and implement the plan as soon as possible with the released amount.

news.title: Delhi government decides to sync construction workers' records with eShram data
news.para: Officials said that Delhi government’s labour department of would develop an application programming interface (API) to access the details of workers registered on the Centre’s portal.

news.title: Amnesty scheme, increase in taxpayers helped Delhi civic body
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) also plans to increase the collection from property tax in the coming years and is awaiting approval for the implementation of professional tax.

news.title: Benefits under PMAY-G provided to deceased persons, ineligible ones: Auditors find in Bihar
news.para: ​Unrealistic geo-tagging of house locations and payment of instalments in wrong accounts are also among the discrepancies observed by teams of the accountant general (AG-Bihar) during the audit of the implementation of the rural housing scheme in the state.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Appeal against society's redevelopment junked
news.para: The bench headed by Chief Justice Sunita Agarwal turned down an appeal filed by 15 members of the society, who were opposing the redevelopment scheme on different grounds.

news.title: Minor building plan changes to be regularised by civic bodies in West Bengal
news.para: As per the notification, a deviation from the sanctioned linear dimensions of parts of a building up to 5%, without change in the internal arrangements, will be considered minor deviation.

news.title: DVAC to probe PMAY fund scam, Tamil Nadu government informs Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing a contempt petition by K Udhayakumar who had filed a public interest litigation earlier complaining about the alleged fund misappropriation by Lalgudi panchayat union officials.

news.title: Pune civic body razes 1.5 lakh sq ft of illegal constructions in green belt
news.para: PMC officials said the administration also removed around 6,000 cubic feet of sand, which was used for reclamation near the riverbank. The sand was transported to Wagholi quarry using six dumpers.

news.title: Only 5% of residential buildings have occupancy certificates: Ranchi civic body
news.para: Out of the 2,451 building plans that were approved by the RMC between 2020 and 2023, only 173 applications for the mandatory occupancy certificates have been received from the builders.

news.title: 'Buildings can fall anytime,' Signature View Apartments RWA tells DDA
news.para: The apartment complex in Mukherjee Nagar, built in 2007-09 with 336 MIG and HIG flats, has some construction issues and is up for demolition by the Delhi Development Authority.
